New Caledonia
) and Christian Mille (Institut Agronomique néo-Calédonien, Station de Recherches Fruitières de Pocquereux, Laboratoire d’entomologie appliquée, La Foa, 
New Caledonia
) were both very enthusiastic and helpful during the sampling of the species in 2003 and 2004. Julio Ferrer kindly translated the abstract to French. This study was economically supported by National Geographic Committee for Research & Exploration (grant 7546-03).
